name: thiazole synthase
reaction: 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate + 2-iminoacetate + thiocarboxy-[sulfur-carrier protein ThiS] = 2-[(2R,5Z)-2-carboxy-4-methylthiazol-5(2H)-ylidene]ethyl phosphate + [sulfur-carrier protein ThiS] + 2 H2O [RN:R10247]
comment: H2S can provide the sulfur in vitro. Part of the pathway for thiamine biosynthesis.
